@startuml activity-sandbox-kill-paths
!include ../_includes/style.iuml

title Activity — sandbox kill paths (POSIX)\nwhat fails the assert vs what voids the measurement

' Disambiguates the FOUR reasons runPythonTests() returns {pass:false}
' vs the SIX reasons it throws SandboxUnavailable. The former is a
' real characterization signal (the model's code didn't work); the
' latter is "we can't trust this measurement" ⇒ UNMEASURED.

start
:characterizeRunner builds\nrunSandbox seam;
:staircase.evaluateItem calls\nrunSandbox({codeLang, code, tests});

if (Provider) then (UnsafeSandbox)
  :throw SandboxUnavailable\n("opt-in off");
  -> unavailable;
elseif (PosixSandbox / WindowsSandbox)
  if (find python OK?) then (no)
    :throw SandboxUnavailable\n("no python");
    -> unavailable;
  endif
  if (mkdtemp + writeFile OK?) then (no)
    :throw SandboxUnavailable\n("mkdtemp" / "write");
    -> unavailable;
  endif
  if (POSIX: setrlimit succeeds in child?) then (no)
    note right : rlimit failures inside\nPython are silently passed;\nthe real failure surfaces\nthrough RLIMIT_FSIZE = 0\nor the wall-clock timer.
  endif
  :spawn child (Python -I -S -B,\ndetached pgrp, empty env);
  if (spawn error event?) then (yes)
    :throw SandboxUnavailable\n("spawn error");
    -> unavailable;
  endif
  fork
    :Wait for `close`;
  fork again
    :Wall-clock timer\n(timeoutMs default 10 s);
    if (Elapsed?) then (yes)
      :kill(-pgid, SIGKILL);
      :reason = 'timeout';
    endif
  fork again
    :Output watcher\n(maxOutputBytes default 1 MB);
    if (Threshold reached?) then (yes)
      :kill(-pgid, SIGKILL);
      :reason = 'output-overflow';
    endif
  end fork
  if (Exit code 0?) then (yes)
    :return {pass:true};
  elseif (Killed by us) then (yes)
    :return {pass:false, reason};
  else (other non-zero)
    :return {pass:false,\nreason:'exit-nonzero'};
  endif
  -> measured;
endif

label measured
:Item recorded with\n{status: pass/fail};
stop

label unavailable
:Caller (staircase) catches\nSandboxUnavailable;
:Item recorded as\n{status:'unmeasured',\nreason:'sandbox-pending'};
:Leaf left as branch prior\n(D12, lower confidence);
stop

note right of measured
  REAL measurement signal —
  enters scores_per_leaf via
  Beta-Laplace (passes_per_leaf
  incremented if pass).
end note

note right of unavailable
  NOT a measurement —
  passes_per_leaf is NOT
  touched (only real climbs
  count toward saturation).
end note

@enduml
